title="A general Nullstellensatz for generalized spaces">Blechschmidt</fr:link></fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {T}]]></fr:tex> be a geometric theory and let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U_{\mathbb {T}}]]></fr:tex> be its generic model in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {Set}{\mathopen {}\left  [\mathbb {T}\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. The <fr:em>spectrum</fr:em> of a <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U_{\mathbb {T}}]]></fr:tex>-algebra <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> is the set of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U_{\mathbb {T}}]]></fr:tex>-algebra homomorphisms <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M\to U_{\mathbb {T}}]]></fr:tex>. (Recall that a <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U_{\mathbb {T}}]]></fr:tex>-algebra is a model of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {T}]]></fr:tex> equipped with a homomorphism from <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[U_{\mathbb {T}}]]></fr:tex>.)</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter><fr:tree
